ValueMeaning.preferredDefinition: The linear extent in space from one end of something to the other end, or the extent of something from beginning to end.

Concepts.definition: The linear extent in space from one end of something to the other end, or the extent of something from beginning to end.

ValueMeaning.preferredDefinition: The weight of the left ventricle in grams as estimated by a formula that uses estimated measurements from echocardiographic exams, as well as constants like the specific gravity of the myocardium. Left ventricular mass is estimated using the following equation, LV Mass (g) = 0.8 {1.04[([LVEDD + IVSd + PWd]^3 - LVEDD^3)]} + 0.6, where LVEDD is LV end-diastolic dimension, IVSd is interventricular septal thickness at end-diastole, and PWd is posterior wall thickness at end-diastole.

Concepts.definition: The weight of the left ventricle in grams as estimated by a formula that uses estimated measurements from echocardiographic exams, as well as constants like the specific gravity of the myocardium. Left ventricular mass is estimated using the following equation, LV Mass (g) = 0.8 {1.04[([LVEDD + IVSd + PWd]^3 - LVEDD^3)]} + 0.6, where LVEDD is LV end-diastolic dimension, IVSd is interventricular septal thickness at end-diastole, and PWd is posterior wall thickness at end-diastole.

ValueMeaning.preferredDefinition: The left ventricular mass divided by the subject's body surface area.

Concepts.definition: The left ventricular mass divided by the subject's body surface area.

ValueMeaning.preferredDefinition: The shortening fraction is a way of measuring left ventricle performance. The shortening fraction measures and ratios the change in the diameter of the left ventricle between the contracted and relaxed states. (from http://www.acor.org/ped-onc/survivors/cardio/cardiotests.html)

Concepts.definition: The fraction of the left ventricle diastolic dimension that is lost during systole; the measurement is calculated using the following formula: (end-diastolic dimension - end-systolic dimension) / end-diastolic dimension; the quotient is then multiplied by one hundred to be expressed as a percent.

ValueMeaning.preferredDefinition: A visual estimation of the volume of blood ejected from the left ventricle during ventricular systole.

Concepts.definition: A visual estimation of the volume of blood ejected from the left ventricle during ventricular systole.

ValueMeaning.preferredDefinition: The percent or fraction of the left ventricular end diastolic volume ejected in systole, which is calculated as the left ventricular stroke volume divided by the left ventricular end diastolic volume.

Concepts.definition: The percent or fraction of the left ventricular end diastolic volume ejected in systole, which is calculated as the left ventricular stroke volume divided by the left ventricular end diastolic volume.

ValueMeaning.preferredDefinition: The fraction of the left ventricular end diastolic volume ejected with each beat. The left ventricular ejection fraction is equal to the left ventricular stroke volume divided by the left ventricular end diastolic volume.

Concepts.definition: The fraction of the left ventricular end diastolic volume ejected with each beat. The left ventricular ejection fraction is equal to the left ventricular stroke volume divided by the left ventricular end diastolic volume.

ValueMeaning.preferredDefinition: The difference between the mean minimum lumen diameter (MLD) assessed immediately after an index procedure and the MLD assessed at follow-up angiography.
